08/04/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Former fashion model Katarina Rebraca has been arrested for allegedly embezzling hundreds of thousands of euros from a breast cancer prevention foundation she heads.
Police also detained four collaborators suspected of helping set up front companies and reporting fictitious payments for medical equipment.
The Katarina Rebraca Charity Fund was set up four years ago and has been raising money for Serbia's first centre for early breast cancer diagnosis.
Police suspect Rebraca stole more than 370,000 euros of donations.
(B92, Blic, Tanjug, Politika - 07/04/10)
